Back to school time means school lunch. I always find myself struggling to come up with good, healthy options for my kiddos to pack in their lunches! That’s where @clifkid Zbars come in! My kids LOVE that they taste like dessert, and I love that they are organic and packed with 10-12g of whole grains to give the kids the right kind of energy they need to get through the school day! I usually plan a shopping trip once every week or two and Zbars are always a staple in my cart!
#ad #CLIFKidBacktoSchool #ClifKidCrew

Weston and I first came to @hotelxcaretmexico in February 2022. It is such a gorgeous and unique resort, and we loved it so much that we were already saying that we wanted to come back before we even left! This time we decided to stay on the adults only side at @hotelxcaretarte and we are again already plotting when we can come back 😂😂 This has definitely become one of my very favorite places to vacation!

If you ever visit Panama City, FL I highly recommend this activity! We booked an excursion through @islandtimesailing and went to Shell Island where we played on the beach, looked for shells, and snorkeled. On the way there and back we spotted dolphins! The captain and crew were so great and the kids had an amazing time.

The one where we went to Salt Lake for 4 hours

This show will always and forever be my most very favorite. The second the suggestion about going down to Utah for the Friends experience was brought up I was all the way in! I am so so glad we did this. Let’s just make it a longer trip next time 😉

Pro tip when visiting Saguaro National Park: every plant there wants to hurt you, and cacti are super prickly (one or three of us may know this from experience 🥴). It was fun to check another National Park off our list, and pretty amazing to see those Saguaros up close! If you are in the Tucson area this is definitely a must-see.
